Company Overview of Loring, Wolcott & Coolidge Fiduciary Advisors, LLP



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Loring, Wolcott & Coolidge Fiduciary Advisors, LLP is a privately owned multi-family office. The firm also provides family office, investment management, estate planning and settlement, financial planning, tax preparation, philanthropic strategies, and ancillary services. It caters to high net worth individuals across generations. The firm also provides its services to individuals, pension and profit sharing plans, charitable organizations, and corporations. It manages separate client focused equity and fixed income portfolios. The firm invests in the public equity and fixed income markets. It invests in the growth stocks to create its portfolios. The firm employs a thematic approach to make...
Loring, Wolcott & Coolidge Fiduciary Advisors, LLP is a privately owned multi-family office. The firm also provides family office, investment management, estate planning and settlement, financial planning, tax preparation, philanthropic strategies, and ancillary services. It caters to high net worth individuals across generations. The firm also provides its services to individuals, pension and profit sharing plans, charitable organizations, and corporations. It manages separate client focused equity and fixed income portfolios. The firm invests in the public equity and fixed income markets. It invests in the growth stocks to create its portfolios. The firm employs a thematic approach to make its investments. It invests in the U.S. treasuries, sovereign debt, and highest-grade general obligation municipal bonds to make its fixed income investments. The firm typically invests in companies with good corporate governance, fair labor practices, employee diversity, and environmental impact. It does not invest in companies related to alcohol, tobacco, gambling, nuclear power, and military weaponry. Loring, Wolcott & Coolidge Fiduciary Advisors, LLP was founded in 1817 and is based in Boston, Massachusetts.
Detailed Description


